description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This Vacancy &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for the right candidate to join our team to deliver training around a number of healthcare skills related topics. The purpose of this role is to:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver and support Trust-wide Healthcare Skills (clinical skills and moving and handling) teaching programmes across the Organisation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide support to the trainers in their local ward / department area, assisting them to implement change&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively support the Learning and Development facilitators, coordinators and subject experts to deliver training by educating a range of staff in all areas and at all levels, networking and sharing best practice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make a collective contribution to the Practice Development function at the direction of the relevant leads within the Learning and Development department&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To support the maintenance programme of all teaching materials, and equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Learning and Development Department is committed to providing all staff and learners at the Trust with access to quality education and training which supports their needs to provide quality patient care. We provide a diverse portfolio of teaching and learning activities using traditional and digital technologies within the department and across the Trust. The department’s work is aligned to the Trust strategies and engages in partnerships with local, regional and national bodies such as Health Education England and we host a number of regional and national projects. This ensures that the Trust is responsive to investing in the training needs of the current and future workforce. The department have received a number of awards and are accredited with the Skills for Health Quality Mark, the UK health sector’s standard for high quality education and training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Practice Development Team consists of a small group of healthcare staff who support the development of individuals and teams across STH and beyond. We do this by supporting staff in all specialties and at all levels of the organisation. We run a number of training programmes designed to help inform practice. These include but are not limited to:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clinical Skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Display Screen Equipment Assessor Training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evidence Based Practice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Moving and Handling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shared Haemodialysis Care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Education in Cancer Care and Long Term Conditions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We also provide an Ergonomic Advisory function, providing advice for staff and managers regarding workplace redesign to accommodate limitations in staff musculoskeletal health, and work with the estates commissioning teams to provide advice for all new build and refurbishment work to ensure environmental considerations for patient care and staff safety are taken into account at the outset.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we looking for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be a motivated person with excellent communication skills. Have a desire to teach to improve practice and have a positive impact on patient care. Have the ability to engage and motivate people. You must be able to work independently and within a team, establish firm links with the clinical skills / moving and handling network and be organized. You must keep up to date. You must be committed to and focus on quality, promote high standards to consistently improve patient outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
